PROGRAM DESCRIPTION
-------------------

Program: smuth (Somatic Mutation Hierarchies)  
Usage:
 -build                  Construct the sample cell lineage trees
 -i <arg>                Input file path (validation or vcf file)
 -o <arg>                Output file path (default: input file path)
 -n,--normal <arg>       Normal sample id
 -minAAFPresent <arg>    Minimum AAF to robustly call an SNV in a sample (default: 0.04)
 -maxAAFAbsent <arg>     Maximum AAF to robustly consider an SNV as absent from a sample (default: 0.015)
 -maxAAF <arg>			 Maximum allowed AAF in a sample (default: 0.6)
 -minGroupSize <arg>     Minimum SNV group size (default: 1)
 -minRobustGroup <arg>	 Minimum number of robust SNVs in group to be robust (default: 2)
 -minRobustGroupKeep	 Minimum number of robust SNVs per group to keep the group in the network (default: 0 - keeps all the groups initially)
 -minTargetDistRatio	 Minimum non-robust SNV to target group's SNV ratio per sample (default: 0.5)
 -e <arg>                AAF error margin (default: 0.1)
 -maxClusterDist <arg>   Maximum mean AAF difference on average per sample up to which two clusters can be collapsed (default: 0.1)
 -minClusterSize <arg>   Minimum size a cluster must have to be considered a node in the network (default: 2)
 -net,--showNetwork      Display the constraint network
 -closestParentOnly		 Only add edges to the ancestor in the closest possible level
 -top <arg>              Number of top ranking lineage trees to display
 -tree,--showTree        Display the top ranking lineage tree
 -v,--verbose            Verbose mode
 -vcf                    Input data type is vcf (default: validation)
 -s,--save               Save the output to file
 -h,--help               Print usage
 -cnv <arg>				 File path to CNV regions used to mark SNVs
 -tcga <arg>			 File path to TCGA SNV annotations
 -cosmic <arg>			 File path to COSMIC SNV annotations
 -ann <arg>				 File path to ANNOVAR variant function annotations
 

HOW TO RUN
----------

./smuth -build -i <input_file_path> - n <normal_sample_id> [options]

EXAMPLES
--------
#Show the top ranking tree
./smuth -build -i ../data/ccRCC/RK26.txt -tree -n 0

#Eliminate clusters that have fewer than 3 SNVs
./smuth -build -i ../data/ccRCC/EV007.txt -n 0 -minClusterSize 3 -tree

#Change hard SNV caller thresholds
./smuth -build -i ../data/ccRCC/RMH004.txt -n 0 -minClusterSize 5 -maxAAFAbsent 0.005 -minAAFPresent 0.01 -tree

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
-------------------
Java Runtime Environment (JRE)


